Reimar Lüst (born 25 March 1923 in Wuppertal, Germany) is a German astrophysicist. He was the director general of the European Space Agency (ESA) from 1984 until 1990. Dr. Lüst received degrees in physics from Göttingen, Chicago and Princeton University and was a professor at New York, MIT and Caltech before he became the director general of the ESA.
